snippet.textDisplay:
First of all, I would pretend I never saw any negative or hateful comments here. And I apologize to everyone here for saying this and wasting your time.

Now, the song itself is beyond beautiful. The lyrics is modernized/improvised/shortened for the sake of the program compared to the original poem written by Shaikh Qalandar Bakhsh Jur'at back in the 17th century and still is beautiful and meaningful. No doubt, the artists who performed the song were equally marvelous. Being a student of music, I can connect to the fact that the song takes the listener to a whole new dimension, which is also evident in all these beautiful comments from all these beautiful people.

Speaking of which, I am touched to see how people are connecting to each other and sharing love and respect from across borders. I am a Bangladeshi but my heart is of an artist who does not believe in borders or differences. We are all people at the end of the day. So, let's spread love and friendship through music.
